Parliament, Monday, 9 September 2019 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will this week host public hearings on the Special Appropriation Bill [B10-2019]. The Bill provides for the appropriation of an additional amount of money for the requirements of the Department of Public Enterprises to assist Eskom Holdings SOC Limited with its financial obligations, and to provide for matters connected therewith. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 10 September 2019
	Time: 9 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Marks Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR Sfiso Buthelezi AND MS DIKELEDI MAHLANGU. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za The seat of Parliament is in Cape Town, but it could be moved by an Act of Parliament supported by a majority of the members of the National Assembly.Read more